  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tzu Chi&#x2019;s Cash for Relief program in Canoa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tzu Chi&apos;s Cash For Relief program in Ecuador is helping Ecuadorians get their lives back on track following the recent earthquakes. Currently, the priority for the people of Canoa is not just rebuilding their own homes, but also working to revive business in the city.

In total, 5,278 individuals participated in Tzu Chi&#x2019;s Cash for Relief program in Canoa, a program that lasted for 5 days from May 17 to May 21. The total dollar amount in USD paid to the volunteers totaled $79,170.00 .

Tzu Chi&#x2019;s Cash for Relief program will continue in other cities and cantons in Ecuador, with Pedernales being the next canton in which the organization will hold the program next.</narrative>
  </description>
